<p><strong>Can I volunteer if I have a disability?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, many organisations are fully equipped to deal with a variety of access and support needs. You can discuss any support needs you have with the organisation you are interested in volunteering with.</p>
<p><strong>Can I volunteer with a criminal conviction?</strong></p>
<p>Many people with a criminal conviction do volunteer, however it is best if you declare any criminal convictions to the organisation that you would like to volunteer with. This will not necessarily mean that you cannot volunteer, but it may limit the roles you can do depending on the nature of the conviction.</p>
<p><strong>Do I need a DBS check?</strong></p>
<p>Whether you need a DBS (Disclosure and Barring Service) check or not will depend on the volunteer role you will be undertaking; usually this will be when you are volunteering for an opportunity that requires working with vulnerable people such as children, elderly or people with mental health difficulties. This is a government run service that checks whether you have a Criminal Record or are on the DBS Barred List. The DBS check is free for volunteers that need it. Further information can be found on the Disclosure &amp; Barring website (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/disclosure-barring-service-check/overview" onclick="javascript:window.open('https://www.gov.uk/disclosure-barring-service-check/overview'); return false;">https://www.gov.uk/disclosure-barring-service-check/overview</a>).</p>
<p><strong>I work for a company – can employees volunteer as a small group?</strong></p>
<p>Yes you can. A successfully managed employee supported volunteering programme can be a fulfilling experience for everyone. Community Impact Bucks enables individuals and groups of employees to volunteer by matching their company’s interest with the needs of the local community or voluntary groups. If you or your employer would like further information on how to get involved, please contact <a href="mailto:info@communityimpactbucks.org.uk">info@communityimpactbucks.org.uk</a>.</p>
<p><strong> Are there any age restrictions to volunteering? </strong></p>
<p>There is no legal age limit, although organisations involving volunteers sometimes have a minimum and maximum age limit, as their insurance policy may not cover certain age groups (such as under 16s and over 80s). However volunteering should be based on the ability of a person to do the role, not their age.</p>
<p><strong>Can I volunteer if I am from overseas? </strong></p>
<p>Generally there should be no problem with an organisation accepting someone from outside the UK as a volunteer, but the individual must ensure that immigration rules allow them to do so. The following link gives further information for European citizens, refugees and asylum seekers and citizens of other countries.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.volunteering.org.uk/images/stories/Volunteering-England/Documents/Free-Information-Sheets/information_sheet_accepting_volunteers_from_outside_the_uk_2012.pdf" onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.volunteering.org.uk/images/stories/Volunteering-England/Documents/Free-Information-Sheets/information_sheet_accepting_volunteers_from_outside_the_uk_2012.pdf'); return false;">http://www.volunteering.org.uk/images/stories/Volunteering-England/Documents/Free-Information-Sheets/information_sheet_accepting_volunteers_from_outside_the_uk_2012.pdf</a></p>
<p><strong>Can I volunteer if my faith means that I need to pray while I am volunteering? </strong></p>
<p>Yes you can. When you talk to an organisation about a potential volunteering role you can ask them what arrangements they are able to make to give you time and a space for worship.</p>
<p><strong>I’ve applied for a volunteer role but not heard anything, what do I do?</strong></p>
<p>The website <a href="http://volunteeringbucks.org.uk/">VolunteeringBucks</a> allows you to apply for a volunteer role directly with the advertising organisation. We suggest that if you have not heard anything back from them within 2 weeks that you contact Community Impact Bucks on 0300 1111 250.</p>

